WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:04.305
Mary:
This is Alice from way back.

00:04.338 --> 00:05.573
Just a kid doing her best

00:05.606 --> 00:09.077
to ignore the implosion
of her parents' marriage.

00:09.110 --> 00:11.545
* I used to bite my tongue
and hold my breath *

00:11.579 --> 00:13.147
Which is why she dreamed me up

00:13.181 --> 00:15.149
in her twisted,
lonely little mind.

00:16.550 --> 00:19.387
* Agreed politely

00:19.420 --> 00:20.388
* I guess that I forgot...

00:20.421 --> 00:22.456
What's up?
Who are you?

00:22.490 --> 00:23.724
I'm Mary, dummy.

00:23.757 --> 00:25.759
And I'm here
because I love you.

00:25.793 --> 00:28.362
With my help, you're gonna kick
life in the A-double-S!

00:28.396 --> 00:29.630
[ Chuckles ]
That's a swear word.

00:29.663 --> 00:31.232
I'll teach you a bunch.

00:31.265 --> 00:33.201
See Mommy?
All sad and broken.
[ Crying ]

00:33.234 --> 00:36.804
That will never be
you, understand?

00:36.837 --> 00:39.073
Go on, say it out loud.
Say it.

00:39.107 --> 00:41.142
[ Whispering ]
That will never be me.

00:41.175 --> 00:42.810
You're gonna be
fierce and independent,

00:42.843 --> 00:44.745
and you will never rely
on any boy.

00:44.778 --> 00:46.280
Or girl.

00:46.314 --> 00:47.848
Your haircut makes things
confusing.

00:47.881 --> 00:51.119
Got it.
Now, let's go smash
something your daddy loves.

00:51.152 --> 00:53.854
Even though Alice's parents
were never there for her,

00:53.887 --> 00:55.689
I always was.

00:55.723 --> 00:57.591
I'm glad your mom
bailed again

00:57.625 --> 00:59.260
'cause that means we can
take the bus downtown

00:59.293 --> 01:00.628
to get our
noses pierced.

01:00.661 --> 01:02.463
Well, your nose.
I don't have one.

01:02.496 --> 01:03.864
Didn't skimp
on the butt, though.

01:03.897 --> 01:04.965
Thanks for that.

01:04.998 --> 01:07.268
Yep, I was turning
that shy little girl

01:07.301 --> 01:08.569
into a kick-ass woman,

01:08.602 --> 01:11.239
which meant, over time,
she needed me less and less.

01:11.272 --> 01:12.773
It's happening.
Our first time.

01:12.806 --> 01:14.175
Hey, don't be so boring!

01:14.208 --> 01:15.609
Flip the script and get on top!

01:15.643 --> 01:16.610
What the?

01:16.644 --> 01:18.679
No! No, no, no!
10 more minutes!

01:18.712 --> 01:20.414
No! No, no!
You still need me!

01:20.448 --> 01:22.850
At least let me get a peek
at his diiii--

01:22.883 --> 01:26.387
* I got the eye of the tiger

01:26.420 --> 01:28.589
Turns out, I had
no reason to worry.

01:28.622 --> 01:31.425
Thanks to me, Alice now
owns her own business,

01:31.459 --> 01:33.627
travels the world,
and is single like a fox.

01:33.661 --> 01:36.330
That is, until this guy
came in for a meeting.

01:36.364 --> 01:38.566
And in 2015, I won
a National Magazine Award

01:38.599 --> 01:41.169
for my --
Online dating profile.

01:41.202 --> 01:42.703
Kudos.
Wha--

01:42.736 --> 01:44.472
[ Computer beeping ]
Clicking out. Um...

01:44.505 --> 01:46.507
"DivorcedRadDad"?
Really?

01:46.540 --> 01:47.875
That's your user ID?

01:47.908 --> 01:50.211
[ Keyboard clacking ]
And we're frozen.

01:50.244 --> 01:51.612
And pulling out the cord.

01:51.645 --> 01:54.182
And...plenty
of battery left.

01:54.215 --> 01:55.115
And we're done.

01:56.250 --> 01:57.451
We'll be in touch.
Will you, though?

01:57.485 --> 01:58.486
No.

01:58.519 --> 01:59.920
[ Telephone rings ]
Know what?

01:59.953 --> 02:02.823
Since this is the worst
interview in history,

02:02.856 --> 02:04.658
can we just go for broke?

02:04.692 --> 02:07.195
My dating profile's
a mess.

02:07.228 --> 02:09.263
You're a PR guru.
Can you fix this?

02:09.297 --> 02:12.733
Since it's everything
a woman isn't looking for,

02:12.766 --> 02:14.468
let's dig in.

02:14.502 --> 02:16.270
First, please,
lose the Crocs

02:16.304 --> 02:17.271
and the braided belt.

02:17.305 --> 02:18.672
Ben: That's
casual Ben.

02:18.706 --> 02:19.773
I'm casual.
You're cute.
Push the cute.

02:19.807 --> 02:22.310
No Crocs, thinks I'm cute.
Got it.

02:22.343 --> 02:23.911
Hey, what do you say
we continue

02:23.944 --> 02:25.112
this work sesh
over dinner?

02:25.145 --> 02:27.948
You do know I was out the moment
I saw you had a kid, right?

02:27.981 --> 02:29.650
Then you're really out
'cause I have frickin' three,

02:29.683 --> 02:31.885
so let's just keep it
professional.

02:31.919 --> 02:34.955
If all goes well, you're
gonna help me fall in love.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.924
Sure, there was
something very charming

02:36.957 --> 02:40.228
about DivorcedRadDad's
complete lack of game.

02:40.261 --> 02:42.896
But my girl knew how
to hit it and quit it.

02:42.930 --> 02:45.766
[ Chuckles ]
I gave it three days.

02:45.799 --> 02:47.235
I was wrong.

02:47.268 --> 02:48.769
[ Telephone rings,
answering machine beeps ]

02:48.802 --> 02:51.339
Andy: Dad? Pick up.
It's an emergency.

02:51.372 --> 02:52.306
[ Telephone beeps ]

02:52.340 --> 02:53.807
Andy? What's up?

02:53.841 --> 02:56.244
There is a poll on our
class Facebook page,

02:56.277 --> 02:57.778
"Most likely to grow up
and be an accountant."

02:57.811 --> 02:59.480
I am leading.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.849
And it's a friggin' landslide!
I voted three times.

03:01.882 --> 03:03.951
Daddy, I lost a tooth
at Grandma's!

03:03.984 --> 03:06.354
Okay, guys, none of this
is an emergency.

03:06.387 --> 03:08.822
But I didn't get any money
under my pillow,

03:08.856 --> 03:10.991
which means
the tooth fairy is dead.

03:11.024 --> 03:12.726
Or she's just
a very busy fairy.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.228
Okay, when are you
gonna be here?

03:14.262 --> 03:14.928
Five seconds.

03:14.962 --> 03:17.531
**

03:20.568 --> 03:22.370
[ Telephone beeps, clatters ]

03:22.403 --> 03:24.004
Put your pants on!
What's happening?

03:24.037 --> 03:25.239
My kids are home.
Who?

03:25.273 --> 03:26.474
My children!
Oh!

03:26.507 --> 03:28.242
Pants. Pants. Whoa!

03:28.276 --> 03:30.278
Pants.
Go, go, go, go,
go, go, go, go!

03:30.311 --> 03:32.613
**

03:32.646 --> 03:33.747
Okay.

03:35.816 --> 03:36.817
Okay.

03:38.786 --> 03:40.020
Yeah, we're on
the second floor.

03:40.053 --> 03:41.455
Babe, you can do this.

03:41.489 --> 03:42.856
You hang down,
stick the landing.

03:42.890 --> 03:44.358
We're really gonna need
a new system

03:44.392 --> 03:45.593
to avoid your kids.

03:45.626 --> 03:46.894
Yeah.
Or you meet 'em.

03:50.964 --> 03:53.301
At worst,
I'd break an ankle.

03:53.334 --> 03:54.968
Okay, listen, the truth is
I want you to meet them.

03:55.002 --> 03:56.570
I want us to take
the next step

03:56.604 --> 03:59.440
'cause you are absolutely
amazing, and I love you.

03:59.473 --> 04:01.909
You got a halfy.

04:01.942 --> 04:03.611
The emotional stuff
gets me excited sometimes.

04:03.644 --> 04:05.579
Oh, God, you're cute.

04:05.613 --> 04:07.481
Let's go for it!
Shut up.

04:07.515 --> 04:08.949
Huh?
Really?

04:08.982 --> 04:10.384
What?
I mean, obviously,
I have to talk to the kids,

04:10.418 --> 04:11.419
make sure that
they're down with it.

04:11.452 --> 04:13.587
Exactly, because
they may not be,

04:13.621 --> 04:15.523
even though I totally
and completely am.
[ Door opens in distance ]

04:15.556 --> 04:16.657
Andy: Dad?
Dora: We're home!

04:16.690 --> 04:17.825
Bunny:
Why do we bury people?

04:17.858 --> 04:18.926
[ Door slams ]

04:18.959 --> 04:20.461
I'm out.
Let me know how it goes.

04:20.494 --> 04:21.462
**

04:21.495 --> 04:23.297
Just like that,

04:23.331 --> 04:24.998
everything I taught her
literally flew out the window.

04:25.032 --> 04:26.934
Meeting his kids
can only lead to heartbreak.

04:26.967 --> 04:28.602
Yeah!
And I cannot let that happen.

04:28.636 --> 04:30.538
Nailed it.
Stuck it!

04:30.571 --> 04:32.840
Lucky for Alice,
help is on the way.

04:32.873 --> 04:35.876
-- Captions by VITAC --

04:35.909 --> 04:38.479
Gather up.
Family powwow time.

04:38.512 --> 04:39.713
I've got a big --
Andy:
I had the worst day.

04:39.747 --> 04:42.316
I need attention now!

04:42.350 --> 04:43.784
Okay, where is this
on the urgency scale, pal?

04:43.817 --> 04:45.586
Anything below a seven,
you handle on your own.

04:45.619 --> 04:47.388
This accountant thing?
It's sticking.

04:47.421 --> 04:48.722
Okay,
that's a hard four, tops.

04:48.756 --> 04:50.524
Kids, the scale only works

04:50.558 --> 04:52.360
when we're honest
with the numbers.
All day,

04:52.393 --> 04:53.594
it was,
"There goes the accountant!"

04:53.627 --> 04:54.728
and "Do my taxes, Holmes!"

04:54.762 --> 04:55.963
See,
this is your whole problem.

04:55.996 --> 04:57.831
Y-You need to be more like
my boyfriend --

04:57.865 --> 05:00.734
complicated, powerful,
a rogue Jedi.

05:00.768 --> 05:02.970
Kylo Ren is not
your boyfriend.
Yet.

05:03.003 --> 05:05.072
[ Andy and Dora yelling ]
Guys? Guys? Guys!

05:05.105 --> 05:06.674
I'm dating a lady!

05:08.942 --> 05:10.978
Her name is Alice,

05:11.011 --> 05:12.880
and I'd love for you
to meet her.

05:14.448 --> 05:17.785
Okay, I can tell this is
a lot, right?

05:17.818 --> 05:20.788
But...
you're really gonna like her.

05:20.821 --> 05:22.656
She's a PR rep
for sports stars,

05:22.690 --> 05:26.927
and she's cool
and funny and sexy.

05:26.960 --> 05:28.796
Which is not something
you tell your children.

05:28.829 --> 05:30.798
The point is, your dad is
kind of nervous, okay?

05:30.831 --> 05:31.999
Does she have kids?

05:32.032 --> 05:33.834
No.
That's just it, Peanut.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.369
She hasn't had all her
coolness drained out of her

05:35.403 --> 05:36.770
the way you guys
have done to me.

05:36.804 --> 05:37.971
Boop!

05:38.005 --> 05:39.907
Uh, sorry, let me
get this straight.

05:39.940 --> 05:42.510
You're dating a woman
whose whole job

05:42.543 --> 05:43.877
is to make someone look better
than they actually are?

05:45.045 --> 05:46.614
Oh, this is perfect
for me.

05:46.647 --> 05:49.883
You can tell Alice --
no, tell A-dogg -- I'm in.

05:49.917 --> 05:51.018
Kind of weird to already
give her a nickname,

05:51.051 --> 05:52.019
but that's a yes.

05:52.052 --> 05:53.687
Who else?
Fine.

05:53.721 --> 05:55.689
Not said with a lot of
enthusiasm, but still a yes.

05:55.723 --> 05:57.525
This is happening!

05:57.558 --> 05:59.993
So this is happening.
Totally happening.

06:00.027 --> 06:01.895
Okay, let's do
a rundown on the kids.

06:01.929 --> 06:03.431
First, Andy --
he's the oldest.

06:03.464 --> 06:05.733
He is very excited
to meet you

06:05.766 --> 06:06.800
and will come on
too strong,

06:06.834 --> 06:08.135
so we need some kind
of a signal

06:08.168 --> 06:09.837
in case he, like,
corners you.
Corners me?

06:09.870 --> 06:11.972
As for Dora, she's
the classic middle child,

06:12.005 --> 06:13.574
Also, a big-time fangirl,

06:13.607 --> 06:15.576
so don't fake your way
through a Harry Potter convo.

06:15.609 --> 06:16.944
You will lose.

06:16.977 --> 06:18.779
Then there's Bunny --
the little one.

06:18.812 --> 06:20.881
Likes to ask a lot
of philosophical
questions about death.

06:20.914 --> 06:22.783
Do not engage.

06:22.816 --> 06:24.418
Table-side guac
coming your way, señor.

06:24.452 --> 06:26.487
iHola! Don't go
loco on me, girl.

06:26.520 --> 06:27.921
Mary's back to help.

06:27.955 --> 06:30.624
[ Gurgles, sniffs ]
What the -- Holy --

06:30.658 --> 06:32.826
I know, how cool is this, right?
They make it right at the table.

06:32.860 --> 06:35.496
Kids? Huge step.
You're spinning out bad.

06:35.529 --> 06:36.797
That's why you dug me
out of your brain.

06:36.830 --> 06:38.632
But don't worry.
We'll handle it together!

06:38.666 --> 06:40.033
This isn't happening.

06:40.067 --> 06:42.436
It's just an appetizer.
Are you okay?
He's onto you.

06:42.470 --> 06:44.505
Pick up your phone like
you have a work emergency!

06:44.538 --> 06:46.106
Work emergency.

06:46.139 --> 06:49.543
Some...public-relations
guys need my help

06:49.577 --> 06:50.944
with some PR stuff.

06:50.978 --> 06:52.079
I got to go.

06:52.112 --> 06:53.814
Love you.
Bye.

06:53.847 --> 06:55.048
Hasta luego, beardy.

06:55.082 --> 06:56.517
Wait.
You're running from me?

06:56.550 --> 06:58.085
Okay, now you're
just being rude.

06:58.118 --> 07:00.688
No hug. No kiss.
This is not how I raised you.

07:00.721 --> 07:02.456
You're just in my head.

07:02.490 --> 07:03.557
Go away.

07:03.591 --> 07:04.958
Slow down!
I can't keep up!

07:04.992 --> 07:06.760
Do not make me
gorilla this.

07:06.794 --> 07:08.829
Why'd you have to give me
these damn stumpy legs?

07:08.862 --> 07:10.764
I cannot hear things
that don't exist.

07:10.798 --> 07:12.065
* La la la la la la la

07:12.099 --> 07:15.102
[ Out-of-tune guitar strumming ]

07:17.004 --> 07:19.707
[ Sighs ]
You a real.

07:19.740 --> 07:21.709
Technically, imaginary,

07:21.742 --> 07:24.144
but to you, I'm real as hell
and here to stay.

07:24.177 --> 07:25.646
[ Laughs ]
Look at us.

07:25.679 --> 07:27.047
The besties are back.

07:30.718 --> 07:32.520
My bestie is back.

07:32.553 --> 07:33.787
**

07:33.821 --> 07:36.590
Oh, my God.
You're back.

07:36.624 --> 07:38.058
Which brings me
to why I am here.

07:38.091 --> 07:39.627
Ben.

07:39.660 --> 07:41.261
He is so cute and kind,

07:41.294 --> 07:42.262
and you have to run.

07:42.295 --> 07:43.964
What? Why?

07:43.997 --> 07:45.933
Look, Ben is a dad.
[ Grunts ]

07:45.966 --> 07:47.167
That means,
if you're with him

07:47.200 --> 07:49.803
[Grunting]
you're a mom.

07:49.837 --> 07:51.939
And before you know it,
you're gonna be at a wedding,

07:51.972 --> 07:53.240
and the "Macarena"
is gonna blast,

07:53.273 --> 07:56.677
and you're gonna mom-dance,
just like this.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.546
* I am a mom,
and I do the Macarena *

07:58.579 --> 07:59.747
* Where is my minivan?

07:59.780 --> 08:00.981
* Oh, I'll find it later

08:01.014 --> 08:02.750
Okay, I will never
dance like that,

08:02.783 --> 08:03.984
but I am freaking out.

08:04.017 --> 08:06.119
Let's get down and dirty.
Go.

08:06.153 --> 08:09.156
It's, like,
I don't know how to mom.

08:09.189 --> 08:10.924
Don't know
if I want to mom.

08:10.958 --> 08:12.860
Don't know if a real mom
would use "mom" as a verb.

08:12.893 --> 08:15.295
We're in agreement.
You know nothing.

08:15.328 --> 08:17.865
But I really love this guy.
I don't want to lose him.

08:17.898 --> 08:20.000
Okay, my Mary advice --

08:20.033 --> 08:22.302
you meet the kids,
just not right now.

08:22.335 --> 08:23.804
Listening.

08:23.837 --> 08:25.673
Take two,
three months to study up

08:25.706 --> 08:26.874
on these "children people."

08:26.907 --> 08:28.075
Learn all about them.

08:28.108 --> 08:30.277
Could take a year,
maybe more.

08:30.310 --> 08:32.580
And the longer I put off
meeting Ben's kids,

08:32.613 --> 08:35.549
the more I'm protecting
our relationship.

08:35.583 --> 08:36.917
Exactly.

08:36.950 --> 08:39.587
You're blowing him off
'cause you care so damn much!

08:39.620 --> 08:41.822
See?
This is why you're here.

08:41.855 --> 08:44.124
Lucky for you,
I got a plan.

08:44.157 --> 08:45.325
Ta-da.

08:45.358 --> 08:46.760
Adele tickets?

08:46.794 --> 08:47.828
That must've cost a fortune.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.262
Hottest ticket in town.

08:49.296 --> 08:51.665
Great way to meet
your kids, right?

08:51.699 --> 08:54.134
Um, the concert's
six months from now.

08:54.167 --> 08:55.869
But worth the wait.

08:55.903 --> 08:56.904
Look at the row number.

08:56.937 --> 08:57.905
One.

08:57.938 --> 08:59.707
Look, I get it.

08:59.740 --> 09:01.108
You're meeting my kids.

09:01.141 --> 09:03.644
It's scary,
especially for you.

09:03.677 --> 09:04.745
[ Knocking on glass ]
He's onto us!

09:04.778 --> 09:05.979
Kick him in the nuts
and run!

09:06.013 --> 09:07.114
[ Grunts ]

09:07.147 --> 09:09.349
Me?
Scared of kids?

09:09.382 --> 09:12.586
I don't even hide when people
bring them in here anymore.

09:12.620 --> 09:14.354
I mean, I close my door,
but that's just because

09:14.387 --> 09:15.856
I have a bowl of candy,
and it's kind of like...

09:15.889 --> 09:17.157
it's my candy.

09:17.190 --> 09:18.959
All that matters is
I love you,

09:18.992 --> 09:20.093
and we're in this together.

09:22.262 --> 09:24.598
I'm scared, and the tickets
were a stall.

09:24.632 --> 09:26.066
Traitor!

09:26.099 --> 09:28.335
And look, if you want to wait,
we can wait.

09:28.368 --> 09:30.137
Promise.

09:30.170 --> 09:32.172
I will love you
no matter what.

09:32.205 --> 09:34.141
Unh-unh. Unh-unh.

09:34.174 --> 09:36.309
Unh-unh.
Mnh-mnh.

09:36.343 --> 09:38.679
And...we're done.
Thank you.

09:38.712 --> 09:40.113
That was disgusting.

09:40.147 --> 09:41.214
You know what?
You already talked to the kids.

09:41.248 --> 09:43.150
Let's do this.
[ Groans ]
Thank God.

09:43.183 --> 09:44.852
Canceling would've been
hard to explain.

09:44.885 --> 09:46.954
They are super suspicious
and awful with change.

09:46.987 --> 09:48.722
They sound great.
So...

09:48.756 --> 09:50.023
what should we do?

09:50.057 --> 09:51.024
[ Gasps ]
Disney World.

09:51.058 --> 09:53.160
We could fly
to Disney World.

09:53.193 --> 09:54.094
It's a big swing --

09:54.127 --> 09:56.029
more of a huge vacation
than a first meet.

09:56.063 --> 09:57.097
Gun range.
Gun range!

09:57.130 --> 09:58.365
Gotcha.
What?

09:58.398 --> 10:02.135
...is something a crazy
person would suggest.

10:02.169 --> 10:04.738
I meant to say...
burgers?

10:04.772 --> 10:06.139
Perfect.
And maybe some mini-golf?

10:06.173 --> 10:07.675
Sounds fun.
Sounds awful.

10:07.708 --> 10:08.676
Ben:
All right, I got to run.

10:08.709 --> 10:09.977
Okay.

10:10.010 --> 10:11.278
We will swing
by your place around 6:00,

10:11.311 --> 10:12.780
grab some chow,
then hit the links.

10:12.813 --> 10:14.782
Wait.
My place?

10:15.983 --> 10:17.084
What just happened?

10:17.117 --> 10:18.919
This -- mom dance.

10:18.952 --> 10:22.389
[ Vocalizing "Macarena" ]

10:22.422 --> 10:24.224
[ Body thuds ]
[ Grunts ]

10:24.257 --> 10:25.793
* Hey, Macarena

10:29.730 --> 10:31.264
It's okay.
No need to panic.

10:31.298 --> 10:32.399
I deal with pro athletes.

10:32.432 --> 10:34.034
They're huge babies.

10:34.067 --> 10:36.103
A few kids?
I've got this.

10:36.136 --> 10:37.805
You so got this!

10:37.838 --> 10:39.272
Okay, I do not.
I am panicking.

10:39.306 --> 10:41.074
Come on. Do what you do.
Coddle me.

10:41.108 --> 10:42.843
Make me feel good.
Give me advice. Go.

10:42.876 --> 10:43.911
[ Doorbell rings ]
[ Whimpers ]

10:43.944 --> 10:45.212
Kids like ice cream.

10:45.245 --> 10:47.781
Sorry.
That's all I got.

10:47.815 --> 10:49.316
Hi.
Hi.

10:50.383 --> 10:51.852
Oh.

10:51.885 --> 10:53.754
Okay.

10:53.787 --> 10:55.288
**

10:55.322 --> 10:57.457
So, uh, guys,
this is Alice.

10:57.490 --> 10:58.959
This is Dora and Bunny.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.260
Nice to meet you.

11:00.293 --> 11:03.163
Damn!
Sweet pad you got here.

11:03.196 --> 11:04.798
How much you lay down?
Like, two, three hundo?

11:04.832 --> 11:06.700
Let's hang.
I'm Andy.

11:06.734 --> 11:08.401
That's my son.
Mm-hmm.

11:12.339 --> 11:13.707
Go.

11:16.043 --> 11:17.911
Hey, need some advice.

11:17.945 --> 11:20.113
So, there is this guy in my
class that sells pot brownies.

11:20.147 --> 11:21.214
Do you think being
a spaced-out burner

11:21.248 --> 11:22.783
would change
public perception of me?

11:22.816 --> 11:24.918
And keep in mind,
I am struggling socially.

11:24.952 --> 11:28.055
I'm gonna say
don't do drugs.

11:28.088 --> 11:30.390
Copy that. Okay.

11:30.423 --> 11:32.793
Personal question.
What was the last one?

11:32.826 --> 11:35.829
On my computer, I have this
folder marked "math homework,"

11:35.863 --> 11:37.831
but it's just boobs.

11:37.865 --> 11:39.032
Where is your dad?

11:39.066 --> 11:40.300
Now, give me the honest,

11:40.333 --> 11:42.035
objective,
female perspective.

11:42.069 --> 11:43.036
Am I normal?

11:43.070 --> 11:44.738
Yes.

11:44.772 --> 11:46.874
[ Slapping counter ]

11:46.907 --> 11:48.408
Knew it!
[ Laughs ]

11:48.441 --> 11:50.811
Man, it feels so good
to rap with someone who gets me.

11:50.844 --> 11:53.280
Now, about my folder
marked "Spanish" --

11:53.313 --> 11:55.148
Ben: All right.
Oh, thank God.

11:55.182 --> 11:56.416
It's getting late.
We should probably order dinner,

11:56.449 --> 11:58.518
and also not serve ice cream.

11:58.551 --> 12:00.487
We'll sidebar on this later,
A-dogg. [ Clicks tongue ]

12:00.520 --> 12:02.422
[ Chuckling ]
"A-dogg."

12:02.455 --> 12:03.924
Nicknames.
That's kind of fast.

12:03.957 --> 12:05.993
Just roll with it.
He's the easy sale.

12:06.026 --> 12:07.460
No, he's great.
He's fine.

12:07.494 --> 12:09.129
He's very open,
he bangs things.

12:09.162 --> 12:12.132
Girls are my specialty
because I was a girl.

12:12.165 --> 12:13.066
I am a girl. Like,
I should probably just,

12:13.100 --> 12:14.067
like, focus on them.

12:14.101 --> 12:15.769
I'd tread carefully.

12:15.803 --> 12:18.338
Bunny's going through
a death phase, and Dora...

12:18.371 --> 12:21.174
I know I shouldn't say this,
couldn't love her more,

12:21.208 --> 12:23.210
but if I had to rank them,
she would be like...

12:23.243 --> 12:25.178
Dora:
Hey, Dad.
...right here!

12:25.212 --> 12:27.848
Hey, Dora.
I had an idea.

12:27.881 --> 12:29.316
I was thinking maybe
next weekend, you and I --

12:29.349 --> 12:31.118
Oh, I'm gonna stop you
right there.

12:31.151 --> 12:33.954
I don't do manis, pedis,
shopping, or Gosling movies.

12:33.987 --> 12:36.824
Oh, um, also,
Andy just ruined your fancy rug.

12:36.857 --> 12:38.191
He makes me smile.

12:41.594 --> 12:44.164
Oh, my --
what the hell, Andy?

12:44.197 --> 12:45.198
Little spill.

12:45.232 --> 12:46.466
Where's your shirt,
dude?

12:46.499 --> 12:48.468
I panicked and used it as a rag,

12:48.501 --> 12:50.337
and no one look at my middle.
I am working on it.

12:50.370 --> 12:51.872
Bunny:
Daddy, look!

12:51.905 --> 12:53.974
I'm Elvis right before he died
on the toilet.

12:54.007 --> 12:55.843
Oh, careful.
That's a vintage Les Paul.

12:55.876 --> 12:57.044
What does this thing do?

12:57.077 --> 12:58.812
[ Alice gasps ]
[ Wawa bar clatters ]

12:58.846 --> 13:00.147
Andy:
Oh, good.

13:00.180 --> 13:01.982
That is way worse
than what I did.

13:02.015 --> 13:03.183
Please don't hate me.

13:04.151 --> 13:05.452
No.
She paused.

13:05.485 --> 13:07.087
She hates me.
Oh!

13:07.120 --> 13:08.488
Andy:
Oh, God.

13:08.521 --> 13:10.457
Someone just tweeted
the Facebook poll.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.926
They're calling me "Blandy."

13:12.960 --> 13:16.196
It's a combination of my name
and the word bland.

13:16.229 --> 13:17.497
Blandy.

13:17.530 --> 13:20.868
Why do my peers always
come up with insults

13:20.901 --> 13:23.971
that are so clever
and smart?

13:24.004 --> 13:25.205
Why?

13:25.238 --> 13:27.207
Bud, I know this whole thing
sucks right --

13:27.240 --> 13:28.842
Okay,
that's a lady's jacket.

13:28.876 --> 13:31.344
Ugh!
Alice, I need you.

13:31.378 --> 13:33.446
Did he just ask for me?

13:33.480 --> 13:36.049
Mm-hmm.
He's really taken to you.

13:37.350 --> 13:38.818
You okay?

13:40.353 --> 13:42.990
I'm just so tired of everyone
looking at me like a nobody.

13:43.023 --> 13:44.524
If you don't like
how people see you,

13:44.557 --> 13:46.927
just make them see
something else.

13:46.960 --> 13:47.928
What do you mean?

13:47.961 --> 13:49.496
She means
change everything.

13:49.529 --> 13:50.630
Reinvent yourself
a little.

13:50.663 --> 13:52.099
Extensive
plastic surgery.

13:52.132 --> 13:53.233
Get a new hairstyle.

13:53.266 --> 13:55.502
Be anyone but you.

13:55.535 --> 13:57.170
Maybe run
for class office.

13:57.204 --> 13:59.272
So, start over as a person?
That's your advice?

13:59.306 --> 14:01.041
[ Grunts ]
See? He gets it.

14:01.074 --> 14:02.409
We're good.
No.

14:02.442 --> 14:05.112
[ Chuckles ]
You are having a PR crisis.

14:05.145 --> 14:06.046
Give me your phone.

14:06.079 --> 14:07.280
Uh, no, I don't...

14:07.314 --> 14:09.282
Trust me.
This is my business.

14:09.316 --> 14:11.952
All you got to do is...

14:11.985 --> 14:14.621
Boom.
And problem solved.

14:14.654 --> 14:15.889
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

14:15.923 --> 14:17.891
Someone just retweeted me.

14:17.925 --> 14:18.959
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

14:18.992 --> 14:20.928
And again.
What did you say?

14:20.961 --> 14:22.930
"Blandy in the house,
y'all."

14:22.963 --> 14:24.531
Wait.
What?

14:24.564 --> 14:26.199
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
"Making life
bland as balls.

14:26.233 --> 14:30.003
#BlandyAsBalls!
#Blessed!"

14:30.037 --> 14:32.172
Oh, no, no, no, no.
W-Why would I say this about me?

14:32.205 --> 14:34.307
'Cause you're taking
the power away from them.

14:34.341 --> 14:36.076
Oh, they are tweeting
me back so fast.

14:36.109 --> 14:37.310
And mean!

14:37.344 --> 14:39.179
Oh, my God!
Okay, we can handle this.

14:39.212 --> 14:41.014
Oh, my God.
They're awful.

14:41.048 --> 14:43.316
Okay. We'll just say that
your phone was hacked,

14:43.350 --> 14:46.219
and then we'll check you into
the hospital for exhaustion.

14:46.253 --> 14:48.255
Wha--
I'm not Lamar Odom!

14:48.288 --> 14:49.522
I am a boy!

14:49.556 --> 14:50.657
Not in that jacket you ain't.

14:50.690 --> 14:52.492
You just ruined my life
in one minute!

14:52.525 --> 14:53.927
Thanks a lot!

14:55.662 --> 14:57.430
Mary:
Okay.

14:57.464 --> 15:00.167
The way I see it,
these are garbage children.

15:00.200 --> 15:02.369
It's not them, it's me.
What happened?

15:02.402 --> 15:04.637
Want to know what just happened?
I just broke Andy.

15:04.671 --> 15:07.274
I broke your child.
I broke him good.

15:07.307 --> 15:09.409
And he was the only one
who even gave me a chance!

15:09.442 --> 15:10.577
Bunny turned on me
for no reason.

15:10.610 --> 15:13.380
It's perfectly natural
to pause

15:13.413 --> 15:15.248
when somebody destroys
your favorite thing.

15:15.282 --> 15:17.450
And Dora?
She's a nerd, dude.

15:17.484 --> 15:20.253
And I like nerds,
but she's a mean nerd.

15:20.287 --> 15:22.455
Whoa. Time out. Okay.
You can't rip on my kids.

15:22.489 --> 15:23.623
Only I can do that.

15:23.656 --> 15:25.525
I can't do this.

15:25.558 --> 15:27.694
I thought that I could,
and I can't.

15:27.727 --> 15:29.396
The way Andy
just looked at me?

15:29.429 --> 15:32.499
I won't do to your kids
what my parents did to me.

15:32.532 --> 15:34.534
Alice, what are you--
You're not your parents.

15:34.567 --> 15:36.736
I am.

15:36.769 --> 15:38.538
[ Sighs ]
I'm sorry.

15:38.571 --> 15:39.672
W-What?
Y-You want us to go?

15:39.706 --> 15:41.308
Is that what you want?

15:41.341 --> 15:43.543
[ Scoffs ]

15:43.576 --> 15:45.645
Okay.

15:47.680 --> 15:50.050
[ Sighs ]

15:50.083 --> 15:51.284
I need a drink.

15:51.318 --> 15:52.986
Alice,
I know you're upset,

15:53.020 --> 15:55.222
but a drink won't fix
anything.

15:55.255 --> 15:56.756
Now, 10 drinks...

15:56.789 --> 15:58.391
Chug! Chug!
Chug! Chug!

16:00.260 --> 16:01.428
* Hands up in the air

16:01.461 --> 16:03.130
And another!

16:03.163 --> 16:04.231
How's my twerk?

16:04.264 --> 16:06.366
Look at me.
Alice, look at me!

16:06.399 --> 16:08.401
Yeah, it's good!
How's mine?

16:08.435 --> 16:10.503
And another! Do it!

16:10.537 --> 16:13.573
* Don't go breaking my heart

16:13.606 --> 16:16.276
* I couldn't if I tried

16:18.145 --> 16:21.214
* Oh, honey,
if I get restless *

16:21.248 --> 16:24.284
**

16:27.054 --> 16:28.421
* Don't go breaking
my heart *

16:28.455 --> 16:30.723
Man:
Off the stage, lady!

16:30.757 --> 16:31.991
* Say you got to give it to 'em,
give it to 'em faster *
Whoo!

16:32.025 --> 16:33.626
* Get a little rude, too,
bring it in hot *
Whoo! Whoo-hoo!

16:33.660 --> 16:35.428
[ Yells ]

16:35.462 --> 16:37.430
[ Crowd groans, music stops ]

16:38.598 --> 16:40.567
[ Cheers and applause ]

16:40.600 --> 16:42.069
Whoo!

16:42.102 --> 16:43.570
Uh-oh.
Uh-oh!

16:43.603 --> 16:46.173
Keep it in your mouth
like a lady!

16:46.206 --> 16:47.740
That's my girl!
Whoo!

16:47.774 --> 16:48.575
[ Body thuds ]
Uh-oh.

16:51.244 --> 16:54.114
I'm gonna need a taco,
and a queso chango,

16:54.147 --> 16:56.449
and an enchiloco!

16:56.483 --> 16:59.119
Oh, my God, I love
street enchilocos!

16:59.152 --> 17:00.187
[ Tires screech, horn honks ]

17:00.220 --> 17:01.388
Hey!

17:01.421 --> 17:03.423
I'm walkin' here!

17:03.456 --> 17:05.024
Yeah, she's
walking here!

17:07.327 --> 17:11.198
Both:
We are living so hard right now!

17:11.231 --> 17:14.201
[ Groans ]

17:14.234 --> 17:17.704
Never drinking again.

17:17.737 --> 17:20.140
Mary: Not even a nice
glass of Chardonnay?

17:20.173 --> 17:22.475
'Cause sometimes a lady
has to let off steam.

17:22.509 --> 17:25.245
What the-- why are
you spooning me?

17:25.278 --> 17:26.813
I like
snuggles, chica.

17:26.846 --> 17:28.715
Why you got to
make this weird now?

17:28.748 --> 17:31.718
Ohh.
What happened last night?

17:31.751 --> 17:33.853
Well, let's see, there was
drinking and dancing

17:33.886 --> 17:36.689
and singing, and driving
Ben away and the bull!

17:36.723 --> 17:37.724
[ Laughs ]
You rode a bull!

17:37.757 --> 17:40.660
Oh, no.
Ben.

17:40.693 --> 17:42.862
I ruined everything.
Ohh.

17:42.895 --> 17:44.864
But isn't that why
I'm here?

17:44.897 --> 17:46.566
'Cause deep down,
you knew this couldn't work?

17:46.599 --> 17:48.101
He had to go, right?

17:48.135 --> 17:50.403
No, I think deep down,
I'm just scared.

17:50.437 --> 17:52.339
No, no, no, no,
p-please don't cry.

17:52.372 --> 17:53.806
[ Sniffles ]
Please?
We can fix this!

17:53.840 --> 17:55.708
How?
How do we fix this?

17:55.742 --> 17:57.510
I got it!
Go to him.

17:57.544 --> 17:59.379
Go to him.

17:59.412 --> 18:02.115
Yes, that's what people do
in situations like this!

18:02.149 --> 18:03.283
And you
apologize.

18:03.316 --> 18:04.751
And beg for forgiveness.

18:04.784 --> 18:07.120
And kiss him long and hard,
and let me watch.

18:07.154 --> 18:08.188
Let's move.

18:08.221 --> 18:09.589
Shoe.
I only have one shoe.

18:09.622 --> 18:11.224
Shoe. Shoe.

18:11.258 --> 18:12.625
Here, shooey,
shooey, shooey.
Hello?

18:12.659 --> 18:14.527
Wha--

18:14.561 --> 18:15.728
[ Exhales sharply ]

18:15.762 --> 18:17.630
You're here?
He's here?

18:17.664 --> 18:19.466
Ben: I wanted to make sure
you got home okay.

18:19.499 --> 18:22.302
You pocket dialed me and left
a three-hour voice mail.

18:22.335 --> 18:24.204
Really tore up the town
after you ditched us, huh?

18:24.237 --> 18:25.405
We can explain.

18:25.438 --> 18:27.707
When Alice was 6 years ol--
[ Body thuds ]

18:27.740 --> 18:29.676
Alice, you cut and run
last night.

18:29.709 --> 18:32.145
That's something I
can't have, not for me,

18:32.179 --> 18:34.147
and especially not for my kids,
you understand?

18:34.181 --> 18:36.883
[ Voice breaking ]
I get it.

18:36.916 --> 18:39.419
I blew it.

18:39.452 --> 18:40.653
It's over.

18:40.687 --> 18:42.755
What? Over?

18:42.789 --> 18:44.157
No.

18:44.191 --> 18:45.592
This is a fight.

18:45.625 --> 18:46.659
We're having a fight.

18:46.693 --> 18:48.395
So it's not over?

18:48.428 --> 18:49.896
Oh, my God,
you have no idea

18:49.929 --> 18:50.830
what you're doing
at all, do you?

18:50.863 --> 18:52.599
[ Laughs ]
I really don't.

18:55.368 --> 18:57.270
Look, I know I messed
up last night,

18:57.304 --> 18:58.538
but there's this voice
in my head,

18:58.571 --> 19:00.873
and it really got to me.

19:00.907 --> 19:03.210
I know the voice, Al.
Eh.

19:03.243 --> 19:05.445
The fear, the doubt.

19:05.478 --> 19:06.713
I have it, too.
Everyone does.

19:06.746 --> 19:10.283
This one's really,
really loud.

19:10.317 --> 19:12.252
Well, there's
another voice now --

19:12.285 --> 19:13.720
mine --

19:13.753 --> 19:17.324
and it is telling you
that we can make this work.

19:17.357 --> 19:19.392
**

19:19.426 --> 19:21.728
You're way too good
for me.

19:24.764 --> 19:26.599
Okay, looks like
we're back on track,

19:26.633 --> 19:29.636
so I'll just give you two
your privacy.

19:29.669 --> 19:32.305
Pretending to walk away...

19:32.339 --> 19:34.307
and show time.

19:34.341 --> 19:36.509
**

19:36.543 --> 19:40.247
Well, it's coarse
to the touch

19:40.280 --> 19:41.914
and doesn't match anything,
but it won't stain

19:41.948 --> 19:43.983
'cause it's made
with chemicals.

19:44.016 --> 19:46.886
Um, I wrote a note
for you.

19:49.489 --> 19:52.425
"Sorry I hurt
your guitar.

19:52.459 --> 19:53.960
Love, Bunny."

19:55.628 --> 19:58.831
Bunny, there's no reason
for you to be sorry.

19:58.865 --> 20:01.200
I know it was an accident.

20:04.937 --> 20:07.807
[ Sighs ]

20:07.840 --> 20:09.876
**

20:15.482 --> 20:16.783
[ Whispering ] You misspelled
some of the words

20:16.816 --> 20:17.984
to look extra cute,
didn't you?

20:20.052 --> 20:22.722
Lot of bonding over here
if either of you guys
want to get in on this.

20:22.755 --> 20:23.956
I'll pass.
I'm good.
Okay.

20:26.459 --> 20:27.760
Look, if you're
open to it,

20:27.794 --> 20:29.962
I would love a redo
of our night out.

20:29.996 --> 20:31.898
Both:
* Don't go breaking
my heart... *

20:31.931 --> 20:34.000
How is this
winning us over?

20:34.033 --> 20:36.336
So this is Alice today --

20:36.369 --> 20:38.438
ruining our duet,

20:38.471 --> 20:41.341
but finally taking
a chance on love.

20:41.374 --> 20:43.576
What you want
is never gonna happen.

20:43.610 --> 20:46.045
* Oh, yes,
it's gonna happen *

20:46.078 --> 20:48.381
Good thing I have her back

20:48.415 --> 20:50.683
'cause she clearly has no idea
what she's doing.

20:52.585 --> 20:53.886
This doesn't mean
I totally forgive you.

20:55.087 --> 20:57.490
* Gave you my heart

20:57.524 --> 21:00.293
Okay, maybe she's figuring
it out a little bit...

21:00.327 --> 21:04.897
Together: * Gave you my heart
...but looking
way uncool doing it.

21:04.931 --> 21:06.333
Mary: Honey,
you are mom-dancing.

21:06.366 --> 21:08.968
Full-on mom-dancing!

21:09.001 --> 21:10.603
* I won't go breaking
your heart *

21:10.637 --> 21:11.971
Oh, come on!

21:12.004 --> 21:14.307
You could still
keep it sexy!

21:14.341 --> 21:15.975
* Don't go breaking my heart
You know, get a little of this.

21:16.008 --> 21:17.477
And then, you know,
one of these,

21:17.510 --> 21:18.511
then some shimmy shake,
and then the old --

21:18.545 --> 21:19.346
Whoo!
[ Thud ]

21:21.548 --> 21:23.950
Andy: Alice, this girl
retweeted me. [ Clears throat ]

21:23.983 --> 21:27.787
"Love the way @AndyLovesTacos--"
that's me --

21:27.820 --> 21:31.691
is owning the nickname Blandy.
#TakingThePowerAway."

21:31.724 --> 21:33.326
Wow.

21:33.360 --> 21:35.428
Who's StonewashedJeans92?

21:35.462 --> 21:36.663
I don't know.

21:36.696 --> 21:37.864
[ Clicks tongue ]
Thanks, A-dogg.

21:37.897 --> 21:39.499
Mm.

21:39.532 --> 21:41.868
Hmm.
StonewashedJeans92.

21:41.901 --> 21:44.103
Sounds like someone's
old AOL screen name.

21:44.136 --> 21:45.738
I threw a kid a bone.

21:45.772 --> 21:47.840
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

21:47.874 --> 21:49.642
Oh.

21:49.676 --> 21:51.678
Andy just sent
StonewashedJeans92

21:51.711 --> 21:52.779
a direct message.

21:52.812 --> 21:54.981
"Hey, girl.
Thanks for the retweet.

21:55.014 --> 21:58.518
Want to meet up IRL?"
Oh, boy.

21:58.551 --> 21:59.919
Both:
And...account deleted.
